Products.RichDescription:
BLUE RIBBON ICE CREAM VANILLA 2 LTR

Treat the family with Blue Ribbon Creamy Vanilla for dessert! Made with wholesome buttermilk and no artificial colours, plus it's 97% fat free!  From the maker of the #1 vanilla reduced fat ice-cream*. Discover why Blue Ribbon has been famously running out since forever and why it doesn't last long in the freezer! Made with Australian dairy, there is a tub or flavour of Blue Ribbon for everyone in the family to create happy memories together.

Blue Ribbon was created by Edwin 'Ted' Streets in 1968, in the small town of Corrimal, NSW. He began by selling his signature buttermilk vanilla ice cream to his neighbours thanks to his wife Daisy and his brothers and today Streets has become one of Australia's biggest and best known ice cream makers. From humble beginnings, Blue Ribbon has come to be Australia's favourite vanilla and now includes some of your favourite frozen dessert flavours like chocolate, Neapolitan, cookies & cream to name a few!

Looking for a serving suggestion? Blue Ribbon goes well with saucy toppings or fruit. It's also fun to eat in cones during summer for nostalgic trip back to bring back childhood memories, however we like it the best just the way it is!

Treat your family and the ones you love with Blue Ribbon's Creamy Vanilla for dessert!

Every tub is made with delicious Australian dairy.

Chocolate reduced fat ice cream made with wholesome buttermilk.
A new delicious creamy chocolate, perfect for any chocolate lover. A delicious dessert the whole family can share!
From the maker of the #1 vanilla reduced fat ice cream*.
Streets Blue Ribbon has been enjoyed by generations of Australians since 1968!
Between World War 1 and World War 2, Edwin (‘Ted’) Street with the help of his wife and brother laid the foundations (in Corrimal, NSW) for what would ultimately become Australia’s biggest and best-known ice cream manufacturer. Streets ice cream was originally made in the back shed by Ted Street. He would then sell these to neighbours along with sweets, cakes and lemonade. Popularity grew and he soon used a cart, then a one horse power motorbike to sell Streets ice cream. It continued to grow and today Streets ice cream is sold throughout Australia and New Zealand with well-known brands such as Magnum, Viennetta, Paddle Pop, Cornetto, Gaytime, Calippo and Blue Ribbon. Today you can still taste Ted's Blue Ribbon special recipe as we continue the tradition of churning rich buttermilk into delicious creamy swirls.
